revision.text:
{{italic title}}
'''''A Bigger Grand Canyon''''' is a 1998 painting by [[David Hockney]] consisting of 60 canvases (in a 12x5 arrangement) that produce one large (7.4m-wide) picture. It hangs in the [[National Gallery of Australia]], which bought it for $4.6&nbsp;million. The [[Cubist]]-type painting portrays the [[Grand Canyon]] in Arizona from many viewpoints and times of day.<ref name="nga">{{cite web|url=https://artsearch.nga.gov.au/detail.cfm?irn=20923|title=Hockney,David&#124; A Bigger Grand Canyon|website=artsearch.nga.gov.au|accessdate=2018-11-08}}</ref>
[[File:Hockney, A Bigger Grand Canyon.jpg|thumb|center|900px|''A Bigger Grand Canyon'', 1998, [[National Gallery of Australia]].]]

